    "body": "I'm taking a look at this. First step is to get a local virtualenv with Python 3.8.\r\n\r\n-----\r\n\r\nDependency `coincurve` has [pre-built wheels for Python 3.8 starting with `v13` (most recent ATM)](https://pypi.org/project/coincurve/#id3).\r\n\r\nUsing an earlier version (like currently-pinned `v10`) doesn't work on Arch Linux: attempting to build wheel results in error of:\r\n\r\n```\r\n    building '_libsecp256k1' extension\r\n    creating build/temp.linux-x86_64-3.8/build\r\n    creating build/temp.linux-x86_64-3.8/build/temp.linux-x86_64-3.8\r\n    gcc -pthread -Wno-unused-result -Wsign-compare -DNDEBUG -g -fwrapv -O3 -Wall -march=x86-64 -mtune=generic -O3 -pipe -fno-plt -march=x86-64 -mtune=generic -O3 -pipe -fno-plt -march=x86-64 -mtune=generic -O3 -pipe -fno-plt -fPIC -I/usr/include/python3.8 -c build/temp.linux-x86_64-3.8/_libsecp256k1.c -o build/temp.linux-x86_64-3.8/build/temp.linux-x86_64-3.8/_libsecp256k1.o\r\n    build/temp.linux-x86_64-3.8/_libsecp256k1.c:493:10: fatal error: secp256k1_ecdh.h: No such file or directory\r\n      493 | #include <secp256k1_ecdh.h>\r\n          |          ^~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~\r\n    compilation terminated.\r\n    error: command 'gcc' failed with exit status 1\r\n```\r\n\r\n-----\r\n\r\n`typed-ast` wheel build fails:\r\n\r\n```\r\n  gcc -pthread -Wno-unused-result -Wsign-compare -DNDEBUG -g -fwrapv -O3 -Wall -march=x86-64 -mtune=generic -O3 -pipe -fno-plt -march=x86-64 -mtune=generic -O3 -pipe -fno-plt -march=x86-64 -mtune=generic -O3 -pipe -fno-plt -fPIC -Iast3/Include -I/usr/include/python3.8 -c ast3/Python/ast.c -o build/temp.linux-x86_64-3.8/ast3/Python/ast.o\r\n  ast3/Python/ast.c:22:1: error: conflicting types for ‘_PyObject_FastCall’\r\n     22 | _PyObject_FastCall(PyObject *func, PyObject *const *args, int nargs)\r\n        | ^~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~\r\n  In file included from /usr/include/python3.8/abstract.h:837,\r\n                   from /usr/include/python3.8/Python.h:147,\r\n                   from ast3/Python/ast.c:6:\r\n  /usr/include/python3.8/cpython/abstract.h:145:1: note: previous definition of ‘_PyObject_FastCall’ was here\r\n    145 | _PyObject_FastCall(PyObject *func, PyObject *const *args, Py_ssize_t nargs)\r\n        | ^~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~\r\n  error: command 'gcc' failed with exit status 1\r\n```\r\n\r\nThis is not a direct dependency; `mypy` pulls in `v1.3.5` (via `<1.4.0,>=1.3.1`).\r\n\r\nInstalling `mypy-0.740` bypasses the issue. Note, though, this version has had [quite some changes](http://www.mypy-lang.org/news.html) compared to currently-pinned `v0.701`.\r\n\r\n-----\r\n\r\n`hypothesis` `v3` has some internal error with incorrect type arg being passed that I don't feel like getting into. `v4` works ~~fine~~ - kind of...",
