    "body": "Working branch in https://github.com/veox/py-evm/commits/add-python3.8-testing - will re-visit later.\r\n\r\nSome stream tests fail due to `hypothesis` picking a very large `int` number that doesn't fit into an underlying `int`. See [`py38-core` job](https://circleci.com/gh/veox/py-evm/4458) (not started ATM).\r\n\r\n-----\r\n\r\nActually, the above job doesn't show that, because [`plyvel` doesn't have a pre-built wheel for Python 3.8 yet](https://pypi.org/project/plyvel/#files); and the CI machine doesn't have the `.h` header file to build the wheel itself.\r\n\r\nFor same reason, all CI jobs that need database access - `py38-{core,database,transactions,vm}` - fail.\r\n\r\n-----\r\n\r\nFurthermore, the `mypy` upgrade has produced quite some new failures in `lint` jobs; see [`py36-lint`](https://circleci.com/gh/veox/py-evm/4439) for example.",
