    "body": "**TL;DR:** We can finally see [`core`](https://circleci.com/gh/veox/py-evm/4633) and [`lint`](https://circleci.com/gh/veox/py-evm/4642) failures - stemming from `hypothesis` and `mypy` updates, respectively. These are present for all of `py36`, `py37`, `py38`.\r\n\r\n-----\r\n\r\nI've tried installing `libleveldb-dev` for Python 3.8 jobs only, using [this wonderful way (commit)](https://github.com/ethereum/py-evm/commit/63683874211720b67247c45aaa7d4819d8deb5e2) (via [CircleCI YAML docs](https://circleci.com/docs/2.0/writing-yaml/)).\r\n\r\nProblem is, [it doesn't work](https://circleci.com/gh/veox/py-evm/4568) for complex value maps: CircleCI only takes the first step. There are topics on CircleCI's forums confirming the fact:\r\n\r\nhttps://discuss.circleci.com/t/yaml-anchors-implementation-incomplete/16916\r\nhttps://discuss.circleci.com/t/allow-bundling-several-steps-e-g-by-supporting-nested-steps/15339/7\r\n\r\n-----\r\n\r\nSo the two remaining options are:\r\n\r\n* install `libleveldb-dev` on _all_ CI jobs, even ones that don't need it;\r\n* wait for `plyvel` to get Python 3.8 wheels.\r\n\r\nI'll now [perform a magic trick](https://github.com/veox/py-evm/commit/8058abd7e03babb6c42e4b2eb71cbffcba9cd84a) by doing _both_ at the same time. :smile: :drum: ",
